# Spring Beans 🌱

## 📖 What is a Spring Bean?

A **Spring Bean** is an object that is created, managed, and maintained by the **Spring IoC (Inversion of Control) Container**.

In simple words:

> **Any object managed by the Spring Container is called a Spring Bean.**

Spring automatically creates the object, injects dependencies, manages its lifecycle, and destroys it when no longer needed.

---

# 🎯 Why Spring Beans?

Without Spring Beans:

❌ Create objects manually

❌ Manage dependencies manually

❌ Tight coupling

❌ Difficult maintenance

With Spring Beans:

✅ Automatic object creation

✅ Dependency Injection

✅ Loose coupling

✅ Better maintainability

---

