# 📦 Bean Scopes

Bean Scope determines how many objects Spring creates.

---

## 1️⃣ Singleton Scope (Default)

Only one object is created.

```java id="sb10"
@Component
@Scope("singleton")
public class Student {

}
```

```text id="sb11"
Spring Container
        │
        ▼
      One Object
```

---

## 2️⃣ Prototype Scope

A new object is created every time.

```java id="sb12"
@Component
@Scope("prototype")
public class Student {

}
```

```text id="sb13"
Request 1 → Object 1

Request 2 → Object 2
```

---

## 3️⃣ Request Scope

One Bean per HTTP request.

```java id="sb14"
@Scope("request")
```

---

## 4️⃣ Session Scope

One Bean per user session.

```java id="sb15"
@Scope("session")
```

---

## 5️⃣ Application Scope

One Bean for the entire web application.

```java id="sb16"
@Scope("application")
```

---

# 📊 Bean Scopes Summary

| Scope       | Description               |
| ----------- | ------------------------- |
| Singleton   | One Bean per Container    |
| Prototype   | New Bean Every Request    |
| Request     | One Bean per HTTP Request |
| Session     | One Bean per User Session |
| Application | One Bean per Application  |

