# 🔄 Spring Bean Lifecycle

A Spring Bean goes through several stages.

```text id="sb17"
Bean Definition
       │
       ▼
Bean Instantiation
       │
       ▼
Dependency Injection
       │
       ▼
@PostConstruct
       │
       ▼
Bean Ready
       │
       ▼
@PreDestroy
       │
       ▼
Bean Destroyed
```

---

# 🏷 @PostConstruct

Runs after the Bean is created.

```java id="sb18"
@PostConstruct
public void init() {
    System.out.println("Bean Initialized");
}
```

---

# 🏷 @PreDestroy

Runs before the Bean is destroyed.

```java id="sb19"
@PreDestroy
public void destroy() {
    System.out.println("Bean Destroyed");
}
```

---

# 💉 Bean Dependency Injection

```java id="sb20"
@Component
class Engine {

}

@Component
class Car {

    private final Engine engine;

    public Car(Engine engine) {
        this.engine = engine;
    }

}
```

Spring automatically injects the Engine Bean.

---

# 🏷 @Primary Annotation

Used when multiple Beans of the same type exist.

```java id="sb21"
@Component
@Primary
class DieselEngine {

}
```

Spring chooses this Bean by default.

---

# 🏷 @Qualifier Annotation

Used to specify which Bean should be injected.

```java id="sb22"
@Autowired
@Qualifier("dieselEngine")
private Engine engine;
```

---

# 💻 Accessing a Bean

```java id="sb23"
ApplicationContext context =
new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(
        AppConfig.class
);

Student student =
context.getBean(Student.class);
```

